<div class="opening" id="artisan">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12">
                <h2>Craft Artisan Team Member</h2>
                <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0026/7229/6025/files/pin.svg?v=1653621832" alt="map pin icon" loading="lazy">
                <span class="mono-type">Location: Columbia, MO</span>
                <p style="margin-top: 1rem;"><strong>Looking for a job you can feel good about? </strong></p>
                <p>
                    SaunaSpace is looking for a Production Team Member to join our passionate team. We're looking for someone with a dedicated work ethic, who can work both independently and collaboratively, exhibits a can-do attitude, and genuinely enjoys learning new things. The ideal candidate will be self-motivated, detail-oriented, and take pride in their work. The role of Production Team Member is essential to supporting our growing operation and contributes in meaningful ways throughout the production process.  
                </p>
                <p>
                    SaunaSpace is a global brand deeply committed to wellness. Combining technology, scientific research, and impeccable craftsmanship, our artisan shop of handcrafted products is on a mission to transform lives. We are equally committed to the wellbeing of our team and support a positive company culture with zero micromanaging and lots of transparency, so everyone actually looks forward to coming to work. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    We welcome people across backgrounds, perspectives, identities, experiences, and abilities, and can't wait to read your application.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Job Location: This is an in-person position at our HQ in Columbia, MO.  
                </p>
                <h3>What You'll Do</h3>
                <p>*Formal training and instruction will be provided</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Effectively and safely operate and maintain equipment and tools with a focus on safety, quality, and meeting production goals
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Operate a LASER engraver, electric cloth cutter, drill press, pneumatic tools, electric hand tools, or manual hand tools and small parts
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Verify work instruction and set-up changes
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Complete preparatory tasks, which may include wire or fabric cutting, fabric manipulation, or other equipment use as stated above
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Quality assurance of processed products
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Manipulate/lift up to 50 pounds as needed
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Ability to stand for up to two hours at a time
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Complete fulfillment tasks such as product packaging, fulfillment preparation, and processing
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Alert management of process difficulties or failures, inventory stock shortages, and equipment or tool maintenance or repair needs
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Maintain a clean, safe, and organized work environmen
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Who You Are</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Have a flexible, adaptable nature and can flow with changing production needs and protocols
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Able to follow instructions and template patterns 
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Detail-oriented, ensuring company specifications and needs are achieved
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Enthusiastic and eager to learn
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        You welcome constructive criticism because you know it helps you grow
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Approach your work like an owner and are willing to help where needed and do what it takes to get the job done 
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Able to maintain efficiency without sacrificing attention to detail
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Reliable in every way, including having reliable transportation
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Able to communicate effectively in English (written and verbal) 
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Conduct yourself with the highest integrity
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Have a high and ever-climbing bar for excellence
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h3>It's a Plus if you're familiar with</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Basic woodworking
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Sewing machine operation
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h3>The Perks</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Employer-paid health, dental, vision, and life insurance benefits package
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Paid vacation
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Paid personal leave
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Full-time, permanent position
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Generous employee discount on all SaunaSpace products
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Holiday pay
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Eligible for a free sauna ($2999.99 value) after 6 months
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Free weekly yoga classes
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Interested, but…</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Think you should apply but aren't completely sure we're a “perfect match?” We encourage you to apply anyway. You miss 100% of the chances you don't take. 
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Application Instructions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Resumes accepted via email or walk-in
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Walk-in applicants should bring their resume or completed application between the hours of 6 a.m. and 3 p.m., Monday–Friday
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Applications may be printed from <strong><a href="https://go.sauna.space/application" target="_blank">https://go.sauna.space/application</a></strong>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Approved applications will be invited to interview by appointment only
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        For questions, call Lacy at <a href="tel:5733701217">(573) 370-1217</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong><a href="mailto:hr@sauna.space">Apply Now</a></strong><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0026/7229/6025/files/a79409d4-email-icon.svg?v=1653623546" alt="email" loading="lazy"></p>
